[{"id":"VH979895","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a horizontal meterstick resting on a fulcrum. There are two objects hanging off of the meterstick. The object near the left end of the stick is labeled m sub 2 and the object near the right end is labeled m sub 1. The left end of the meterstick is attached to a string that goes over a pulley. The other end of the string is attached to an object labeled Object X that hangs from the string below the left side of the pulley.\" height=\"153\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979895.g02.png\" width=\"425\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The center of mass of a uniform meterstick is placed on a fulcrum. Two objects of known mass, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 1\"><math alttext=\"m sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 2\"><math alttext=\"m sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, are hung at known positions on the meterstick. One end of a string is attached to one end of the meterstick, and the other end of the string is looped around a pulley and connected to hanging object <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of unknown mass, as shown in the figure. The meterstick does not rotate and is level with the horizontal. Which of the following measuring devices, if any, should be used to make measurements to determine the unknown mass of object <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>? Justify your selection.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH979895_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A ruler, because the length of the string that is looped around the pulley should be measured.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A protractor, because the angle between the force due to gravity exerted on objects <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 1\"><math alttext=\"m sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 2\"><math alttext=\"m sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and the distance between where the force is applied and the tip of the fulcrum should be measured.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A motion sensor, because the distance per unit of time of object <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> should be measured.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">No additional equipment or measurements are needed, because the force due to gravity exerted on objects <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 1\"><math alttext=\"m sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 2\"><math alttext=\"m sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and the distance between where the force is applied and the tip of the fulcrum are already known.</p>"],"answer":3}]